Task: Create docs/USER_GUIDE.md - unified user guide with CLI reference

Summary:
Created a comprehensive user guide covering all 6 gd-tools CLI commands with
narrative flow. The document includes:

1. Getting Started - prerequisites (Python 3.10+, Godot 4.5+), installation,
   and a 10-step init walkthrough.
2. Configuration - full gd-tools.toml reference covering all 5 sections
   ([godot], [test], [lint], [format], [coverage]) with all keys, defaults,
   valid values, and examples.
3. Command Reference - one section per command (init, doctor, test, lint,
   format, coverage) each with description, usage syntax, flags table,
   examples, and exit codes. Includes the --timeout flag on test (exists in
   implementation but not in spec FR-2). Coverage subcommands: report, merge,
   show each fully documented.
4. Examples - 4 common workflows: first test run, CI/CD pipeline (GitHub
   Actions YAML), coverage threshold enforcement, lint+format in CI.
5. Troubleshooting - 4 common issues: Godot not found, GUT not installed,
   version mismatch (with GUT version map table), coverage not generating.

